Politics of the handshake dominated the speeches as celebrated Kikuyu musician Joseph Kamaru was given a hero’s send -off during a burial ceremony attended by President Uhuru Kenyatta,his deputy William Ruto and opposition leader Raila Odinga. The three leaders who rallied behind the handshake saying it was for posterity eulogised the late Kamaru as a legend,hero and a true Kenyan.The president  also  agreed to chair talks to resolve the crisis surrounding the Ndakaini dam waters.  